definitions.definition: The property of an electric circuit or its element that permits it to store charge , defined as the ratio of stored charge to potential over that element or circuit ( Q/V ); SI unit: farad (F).
An element of an electrical circuit exhibiting capacitance.

main_definition: ( physics , uncountable ) The property of an electric circuit or its element that permits it to store charge , defined as the ratio of stored charge to potential over that element or circuit ( Q/V ); SI unit: farad (F).
secondary_definitions: ( physics , countable ) An element of an electrical circuit exhibiting capacitance.
